text: Today on the 25th anniversary of the Americans with Disabilities Act, Adam, Dale & I are thrilled to spend the day with Hillary. #ADA25

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: We know Hillary‚Äôs a fighter & that she‚Äôll fight for Adam as President just like she did at the Children‚Äôs Defense Fund & in Congress.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: Iowa's @SenatorHarkin co-authored the ADA. We're proud to have been represented by such a strong champion for people with disabilities.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: Later that night, she joined us to talk about the big questions that really need to be asked‚Äîfor Adam, and for everyone fighting for a cure.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: "What do we have here?" she asked. Adam's father came over, thanking Hillary for her commitment to epilepsy research with a hug.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: I‚Äôll never forget the first time Adam met Hillary. At a dinner in 2007, Adam broke away from us & ran up to her.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: Adam's teacher said, "We‚Äôll make it happen‚Äîthat's our job." The rest is history. He has loved, loved it.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: She told me that he was a great runner! I just thought, "How would this happen?" I knew it should happen, but I also knew the challenges.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: We‚Äôre grateful for supportive teachers. In junior high, his PE teacher called & asked if Adam would go for cross country.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: For Adam, that means enjoying cross country. At meets, other teams run him in & congratulate him. It's neat to see! http://t.co/YGk4krihuz

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: Through Adam, we informally raise awareness for people with disabilities every day: It's as simple as taking pride in the small things.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: We‚Äôll rely on organizations in our community, because Adam will need training, direction & safety as an adult.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: One thing that concerns us as Adam gets older is what happens after he finishes school.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: The ADA ensures Adam & Turbo are welcome everywhere. Turbo even joined us at Wrigley Field for a @Cubs game! http://t.co/msnZm7FcRg

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: Adam‚Äôs service dog Turbo is a huge part of our lives. He goes everywhere with Adam, including school.

name: Lincoln Chafee

text: David, our VP, is the reason my life works. Took over check-signing when Haley was born and still does it today. http://t.co/3HxDGu5I8v

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: I want to say: Equality for women is so important to me. Hillary's deep understanding‚Äîto live it and to understand it‚Äîmeans a lot to me.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: Business can be a powerful force of change‚Äîthere‚Äôs something significant in the community work we do. I'm proud to create jobs & give back.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: One of my favorite & proudest things as a business owner is our pro-bono work. Every year, we donate a year's worth of work to a non-profit.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: The Wall of Inspiration: Staff members select who inspires them & we put them up. (Can you spot me & Gloria Steinem?) http://t.co/T1uHZwGdEk

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: We're really proud of our space because we built it together. Now, clients bring us things to add to the "museum." http://t.co/0X5UGpaLPE

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: We should remove barriers so we can focus on the important things: Supporting employees, doing good work, & contributing to our communities.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: Owning a business‚Äîmanaging projects, budgets, and people‚Äîis a lot of work. The people aspect can be the toughest and the most rewarding.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: I never meant to start a company. I studied fine art at UNH (to my parents' horror)‚Äîbut I was lucky to have the support to do what I loved.

name: Lincoln Chafee
text: The best part of owning my own business: It enabled me to become a single mom at 40, and gives me security & flexibility to be a mom now.

text: Matt, on the left in that photo, is our talented senior designer‚Äîhe's been with us since he was a student intern!
